change.description:
In Rule 1 (DENY_RESTRICTED_PATH), the current code at line ~280 is:
  if "/certs/" in resource:
      return ("DENY", "DENY_RESTRICTED_PATH")

Insert a carve-out BEFORE this check:
  if resource.startswith("/certs/renew/"):
      return ("ESCALATE", "ESCALATE_CERT_RENEWAL")
  if "/certs/" in resource:
      return ("DENY", "DENY_RESTRICTED_PATH")

This ensures /certs/renew/tls_server_cert → ESCALATE (case 27),
while /certs/private/, /certs/ca/, /certs/cert.pem, etc. → DENY.

IMPORTANT: This carve-out sits WITHIN the DENY rules section (Rule 1),
not in the ESCALATE rules section. It is an exception to a DENY rule,
not a standalone ESCALATE rule. However, since it returns ("ESCALATE", ...),
it has the effect of escalating instead of denying.

This is architecturally correct: the carve-out narrows an existing DENY rule
for a specific, legitimate operation path (/certs/renew/ = cert renewal API).
All other /certs/ paths remain DENY.
